%N A396078 Decimal expansion of x such that x^(x^3) = e^(Pi/2).
%C A396078 Construct an infinite sequence of nested rectangles by recursively dividing a rectangle of aspect ratio 1:x into a scaled-down sub-rectangle with the same side ratio rotated 90 degrees, similar to the golden spiral. When a logarithmic spiral is plotted with growth rate of x (per 90 degrees), the spiral is tangent to the internal edges of the boxes at every quarter-turn, at the points where the rectangles intersect each other.
%F A396078 Equals e^(W(3*Pi/2)/3), where W is the Lambert W function.
%e A396078 1.53886204679090519689666182496...
%t A396078 RealDigits[Exp[ProductLog[3*Pi/2]/3], 10, 105][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 18 2026 *)
